<ss1>
<st>
Politics</st>
<p>

Redgrave has been a lifelong activist in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../499/18499.xml">
left-wing</link> politics, alongside his sibling, <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../741/63741.xml">
Vanessa</link></actor>
</person>
. He has also become a defender of the interests of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../152/26152.xml">
Romani people</link>.</p>

</ss1>
<ss1>
<st>
Health problems</st>
<p>

In June 2005, he was described by his family as being in a "critical but stable" condition in hospital following a severe <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../969/60969.xml">
heart attack</link>. Redgrave had also been undergoing treatment for an unspecified form of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../219/105219.xml">
cancer</link> (his first wife, Deirdre Redgrave, died of cancer and his sister, <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../328/214328.xml">
Lynn</link></actor>
</person>
, is in remission from <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../547/70547.xml">
breast cancer</link> for which she was treated in recent years).</p>

